label.value: decreased protein localization to mitochondrion, with diffuse cytoplasmic protein mislocalization

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitochondrion is decreased, and the protein is instead visible diffusely localized in the cytoplasm.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cellular superoxide level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of superoxide measured in a cell that is subject to nitrogen starvation is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased microfilament motor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate or other property of a microfilament motor activity is decreased.

label.value: smooth ascospore wall

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the outer surface of the spore wall is smooth, lacking the structures than protrude outward from normal spore walls.

label.value: decreased outer prospore membrane breakdown

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which breakdown of the outer layer of the prospore membrane (forespore membrane; FSM) is decreased. Normally, the outer of the two FSM layers breaks down completely, producing a mature spore. When FSM breakdown does not occur normally, the outer FSM layers of two adjacent spores may be fused.

label.value: decreased DNA degradation during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the breakdown of DNA occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

label.value: delayed onset of mitotic DNA replication initiation during recovery from nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the initiation of nuclear DNA replication begins later than normal when cells are returned to nitrogen-rich medium following nitrogen starvation.

label.value: abnormal RNA localization during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of an RNA in a cell is abnormal during the meiotic cell cycle. An RNA may be observed in a place where it is not normally found, absent from a place where it is normally found, or both.

label.value: abolished tRNA guanosine 7-methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the posttranscriptional methylation of a guanosine residue in a tRNA molecule to form 7-methylguanosine does not occur.

label.value: decreased mitochondrial volume

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total volume of all mitochondria in the cell is lower than normal.

label.value: small fragmented mitochondria present in decreased numbers

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondria are smaller, and the total number of mitochondria in the cell is lower, than normal.  Total mitochondrial volume is therefore lower than normal normal.

label.value: increased transcription from STREP promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more STREP motifs occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased transcription from STREP promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more STREP motifs occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: normal transcription from STREP promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more STREP motifs is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in extent, timing, start or termination site, etc.

label.value: increased transcription from STREP promoter during cellular response to nitric oxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more STREP motifs occurs to a greater extent than normal during a cellular response to nitric oxide.

label.value: sensitive to diuron

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to diuron. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of diuron that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to sodium azide

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to sodium azide (NaN3). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of sodium azide that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: delayed onset of protein export from nucleus

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the export of protein from the nucleus begins later than normal. Export of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to oxidative stress.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to oxidative stress.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein-protein interaction during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to another occurs to a lower extent than normal when the cell is subject to oxidative stress. The relevant proteins may include the one encoded by the mutated gene, or may both be encoded by different genes.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased cellular reactive oxygen species level during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell is higher than normal when the cell is subject to oxidative stress.

label.value: decreased mitochondrial respiratory chain complex III assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of mitochondrial respiratory chain complex III assembly is decreased.

label.value: decreased mitochondrial respiratory chain complex IV assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of mitochondrial cytochrome c oxidase (respiratory chain complex IV) assembly is decreased.

label.value: mitochondrial respiratory chain complex III absent from cell

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which does not contain a detectable mitochondrial respiratory chain complex III.

label.value: normal protein oxidation during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein oxidation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased RNA catabolic process during glucose starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype which the occurrence of an RNA catabolic process is decreased when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

label.value: abnormal chromatin organization during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nuclear chromatin organization is abnormal during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: normal viability during G0

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable during G0 phase.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 acetylation at rDNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at ribosomal DNA occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K12 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 12 of histone H4 occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K16 acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K14 acetylation at silent mating-type cassette during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 at the silent mating-type cassettes occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K14 acetylation at rDNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 at ribosomal DNA occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H4-K16 acetylation at protein coding gene during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 16 of histone H4 in regions containing protein coding genes occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 acetylation at promoter during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at in one or more promoter regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased chromatin mobility

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin moves within the nucleus to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased anisotropic motion of mitotic chromatin

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the anisotropic movement of chromatin occurs to a lower extent than normal during mitosis. Normally, chromatin moves to a lesser extent, and with less freedom of movement direction (i.e. more anisotropically), during mitosis than during interphase.

label.value: increased DNA damage at rDNA during G0

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of DNA damage measured at ribosomal DNA in a cell is greater than normal during G0 phase. The number, extent, or both of damage sites may be increased.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at rDNA during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal at ribosomal DNA during G0 phase.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 methylation during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal during G0 phase.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at rDNA during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal at ribosomal DNA during G0 phase.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at centromere outer repeat during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal in centromere outer repeat regions during G0 phase.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K9 dimethylation at subtelomeric heterochromatin during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a lower extent than normal in subtelomeric regions occurs during G0 phase.

label.value: abnormal chromosome segregation during G1 to G0 transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which chromosome segregation is abnormal during one or both of the cell divisions that a cell undergoes prior to entering quiescence (G0).

label.value: septated mononucleate vegetative cell with mislocalized nucleus and anucleate compartment

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell has one or more septa, and one nucleus that is not in the normal location. The cell also has one or more compartments with no nucleus.

label.value: inviable elongated mononucleate aseptate cell with cell cycle arrest in mitotic M phase and normal nucleus localization

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, contains one nucleus in the normal location, has no septum, and progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in M phase.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to pericentric heterochromatin is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin during meiosis II

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to pericentric heterochromatin is abolished during the second meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to pericentric heterochromatin is abolished during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
